RN  [2]
RM  17600077
RT  Analysis of the aerobactin and ferric hydroxamate uptake systems of
RT  Yersinia pestis.
RA  Forman S, Nagiec MJ, Abney J, Perry RD, Fetherston JD;
RL  Microbiology. 2007;153:2332-2341.
CC  Aerobactin is a siderophore of the hydroxamate class. Four biosynthetic
CC  genes, iucABCD (Iron Uptake Chelate) synthesize it from two lysines and
CC  a citrate. IucD is L-lysine 6-monooxygenase (NADPH) (EC 1.14.13.59).
CC  IucB is N(6)-hydroxylysine O-acetyltransferase (EC 2.3.1.102). The
CC  actions of IucA, followed by IucC, attach two molecules of
CC  6-N-acetyl-6-N-hydroxy-L-lysine to a citrate backbone; it is
CC  convenient, for now, to regard these two steps together as 6.3.2.27.
**  1.14.13.59 2.3.1.102 6.3.2.27
